# Project Documentation Structure

All docs live in `/docs`. Each document has a single responsibility; no overlap or duplication.

| Document | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| **docs/workflow/00_overview/user-flow.md** | Application behavioral flow from user perspective: entry points, navigation, state transitions, auth boundaries, and error paths. |
| **docs/workflow/90_product/prd.md** | What the system must do and why: scope, requirements, acceptance criteria, constraints, and success metrics. |
| **docs/workflow/02_planning/backend.md** | Server-side behavior and architecture: API contracts, data models, business rules, validation, auth, integrations. |
| **docs/workflow/02_planning/frontend.md** | Frontend architecture and behavior (if/when frontend planning is in scope). |
| **docs/workflow/02_planning/file-structure.md** | Codebase organization, module boundaries, file responsibilities, and function-level responsibilities. |
| **docs/workflow/90_product/progress.md** | Development execution state: tasks, status, blockers, implementation notes, and stage checkpoints. |
| **docs/workflow/90_product/project-status.md** | Major capability readiness table and lifecycle state transitions. |

### Supporting / reference docs

| Document | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| **docs/workflow/03_tools_and_mcp/README.md** | Index for MCP docs and ownership boundaries. |
| **docs/workflow/03_tools_and_mcp/agent-tools-reference.md** | MCP tool payloads, samples, and per-agent allowlists; keep in sync with `llm/tool_descriptions.py`. |
| **docs/shared/websearcher-git-sync-notes.md** | Historical git/MCP migration notes only. |
| **docs/shared/test_plan.md** | Test matrix and docs-consistency checklist. |
| **docs/workflow/00_overview/use-case-trace-beginner.md** | Step-by-step function trace for one beginner request. |
| **docs/workflow/git-commit-cohesion-review.md** | Git hooks + pre-commit cohesion/coupling workflow. |
| **docs/workflow/02_planning/dependency-contract.md** | Allowed import direction between packages and ingestion source-of-truth. |

**Optional/if present:** auxiliary docs such as `demo.md`, data-manager design docs, or schema supplements can be used as references, but must not duplicate canonical ownership above.

**Generated:** **api-test-results.md** is produced by `scripts/test_third_party_apis.py`; operational only, not edited by hand.

## Update triggers (when to touch which doc)

- **docs/workflow/00_overview/user-flow.md:** New entry point, navigation/state path, auth boundary, or error path.
- **docs/workflow/90_product/prd.md:** Approved feature/scope change, acceptance criteria update, business requirement change.
- **docs/workflow/02_planning/backend.md:** API/data model/business rule/auth/integration/validation changes.
- **docs/workflow/02_planning/frontend.md:** Frontend architecture/component/state management changes.
- **docs/workflow/02_planning/file-structure.md:** New module, file responsibility changes, function add/remove/refactor.
- **docs/workflow/90_product/progress.md:** Task completion/new task, notable implementation decision, recurring issue and resolution.
- **docs/workflow/90_product/project-status.md:** Capability state changes (Not Started/In Progress/Live/Deprecated).
- **docs/workflow/03_tools_and_mcp/README.md:** MCP doc boundary or ownership changes.
- **docs/workflow/03_tools_and_mcp/agent-tools-reference.md:** MCP tools/payload contracts/allowlists changed.
- **docs/shared/test_plan.md:** Stage test matrix or docs consistency checklist changed.
- **docs/workflow/00_overview/use-case-trace-beginner.md:** Traced request flow/function sequence changed.
- **docs/workflow/git-commit-cohesion-review.md / .cursor/rules/git-commit-cohesion-review.mdc:** Hook install/review workflow behavior changed.
- **docs/workflow/02_planning/dependency-contract.md:** Package layering or ingestion source-of-truth changed.

## Governance

A feature is not complete until PRD, user-flow, backend/file-structure, progress, and project-status are consistent. Documentation integrity is mandatory.
